pr_title: add: requests immersive, clicking Enter VR launches inline
pr_body:
Changes to p5xr, p5xrButton, and p5vr so the sketch launches in inline XR, and clicking Enter VR launches immersive. 
![iss169 base](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/22751315/179459473-0e872e36-7e8c-4a66-bfb6-084f15c97485.png)

pr_body:
Changes:
- Including the [Quaternion.js](https://github.com/infusion/Quaternion.js/) library as a dependency.
- Exposing the rotation as Euler angles (while respecting the `angleMode`) for progress for #158. There is some gimbal-locking type behavior that is persisting.
- Updating the manual input test to show controller tracking with orientation as well as primary and second button presses
- Added notice about gimbal locking to documentation


https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/22751315/186528906-cf60441d-1cab-431e-b950-fecd9eb41ce2.mp4

Here you are using the `isLooselyEqual` comparison operator vs the `isStrictlyEqual` one which is against the linting rules. [Here is a reference on the difference.](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Equality_comparisons_and_sameness)', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 25, 16, 13, 24, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'stalgiag', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 955175711, 'comment_body': 'A good idea to mention the gimbal locking behavior here and provide `applyMatrix(p5xrInput.pose)` as an alternative.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 25, 16, 14, 53, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'stalgiag', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 956375223, 'comment_body': 'removed', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 8, 26, 19, 24, 32, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'smrghsh', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 956376333, 'comment_body': "This function now checks for `angleMode `and uses p5's angle converter. pr_title: add: documentation to help Windows developers to use openssl
pr_body: Windows users should git bash to prevent this openssl error
pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 915260520, 'comment_body': '```suggestion\r\nWith Android Mobile for sketches made for both **AR and VR**, you can run `npm run setup-ssl` on your development computer to create an SSL cert-key pair. Then you can run `npm run dev-server` to start a secure local server. This should result in a message that gives you the IP address for your new secure local server (ex: `192.168.1.104:8080`). You can then add that IP into the URL input in the Chrome browser on your phone and access the p5xr folder from your phone. This allows you to run the `manual-test-examples` on your phone.\r\n```', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 6, 21, 12, 57, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'stalgiag', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 920237917, 'comment_body': 'Would be better to move the object rather than viewer to keep these examples conceptually simple', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 13, 15, 45, 56, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'stalgiag', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 920238586, 'comment_body': 'Probably better to separate these changes from the openssl documentation changes. This commit can be reverted and then a new branch can be made with a new PR.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 13, 15, 46, 35, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'stalgiag', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_title: fix: move objects in front in manual test
pr_body: Moving objects in front of camera for manual tests. Quality of life improvement for debugging, so you don't have to turn your head in VR in order to validate the manual tests
